title: Decrease Pushy heartbeat interval + config refactoring
message:
Decrease Pushy heartbeat interval + config refactoring

Decrease the Pushy socket keepalive interval to every 3 minutes, instead
of the default 5 minutes.

There are home routers that disconnect idle connections after 4 minutes
of inactivity. This will improve reliability, while slightly affecting
battery performance. Hopefully, it won't be noticeable.

In addition, refactored the GCM configuration into a new package
"com.red.alert.config.push", renamed the class to `GCMGateway`, and
created a `PushyGateway` configuration file as well.

title: Disable secondary alerts by default
message:
Disable secondary alerts by default

Users are complaining about receiving "irrelevant" rocket alerts by
default.

title: Fix `RuntimeException` in Android 4.0 devices (Mi Band Integration)
message:
Fix `RuntimeException` in Android 4.0 devices (Mi Band Integration)

Due to a bug in Android 4.0, apps cannot query for the
`BluetoothAdapter.getDefaultAdapter()` from an async (non-UI) thread.

The workaround is to cache the adapter on a UI thread, or call
`Looper.prepare()` on the async thread.

I chose to call `Looper.prepare()` because I donâ€™t have an efficient
way to call `BluetoothAdapter.getDefaultAdapter()` from a
Looper-enabled thread when the application is invoked via a push
notification. I do not have access to an activity with a UI thread in
the push BroadcastReceiver.

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5920578/bluetoothadapter-getdefault-t
hrowing-runtimeexception-while-not-in-activity

title: v1.0.8.6 - Revert Doze Compat (Google Play Policy)
message:
v1.0.8.6 - Revert Doze Compat (Google Play Policy)

Unfortunately, Google Play decided to suspend the app and that the only
way it will be reinstated is if the the
REQUEST_IGNORE_BATTERY_OPTIMIZATIONS permission is removed, even though
I explained that according to the docs I had every right to request it.
I decided to remove it so that I won't risk permanent deletion of the
app.

It seems that Google is extremely trigger-happy and emotionless about
suspending and permanently banning apps on Google Play.

title: Doze Mode & App Standby Compatibility
message:
Doze Mode & App Standby Compatibility

Support Android 6.0 (Marshmallow) devices by adding a dialog that asks
the user to disable doze mode explicitly for RedAlert, so that rocket
alerts may be received in real time (through the secondary push
notification gateway).

GCM push notifications are sent as high-priority anyway, but we want the
secondary push gateway to work as well, just in case.
